"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539684","HM Treasury","false","2016-07-21","<p>Details on individual projects which fall under devolved areas of responsibility are a matter for the devolved administration in Northern Ireland. In light of the UK’s vote to leave the EU, the Government is carefully considering the options for the future of EU-related funding.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-07-21T11:01:54.94Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539684/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539684/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539684/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-07-18","EU Grants and Loans: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which (a) completed, (b) in progress and (c) scheduled projects in Northern Ireland have received or are scheduled to receive EU funding; what assessment he has made of the potential effect on that funding of the vote to leave the EU; and whether any resulting shortfall in funding will be met by his Department or the Northern Ireland Office.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","42991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539685","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-26","<p>We are aware of allegations of the bombing of an Oxfam warehouse on 18 April 2015. It is important that thorough and conclusive investigations are conducted into this incident. We encourage NGOs to share information of incidents of concern with HMG to be considered in the analysis conducted by MOD.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-07-26T15:20:08.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539685/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539685/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/539685/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-18","Yemen: Bombings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the bombing of an Oxfam warehouse in Saada on 18 April 2015; and if he will commission a Government inquiry into that bombing.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","43139"
