"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536478","Department of Health","false","2016-07-20","<p>As recommended by the independent Mental Health Taskforce, the Department is undertaking a five year plan for the development of mental health data to be published by the end of the year. The plan will set out future requirements and timings for developing data to inform pathways of care, which will include requirements for autism in the Health and Social Care Information Centre Mental Health Services Data Set. It is too early to say what form the work on indicators for autism diagnosis will take and how long this will take to complete.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-07-20T13:34:28.283Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536478/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536478/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-14","Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when work on indicators recording a diagnosis of autism within the Health and Social Care Information Centre mental health services data set will be completed.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","42817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536479","Department of Health","false","2016-07-20","<p>Before making its final recommendations the Clinical Priorities Advisory Group (CPAG) undertakes a final check to consider whether any adjustments should be made to its initial recommendations. It may give a treatment a higher priority, if it decides the treatment significantly:</p><p> </p><p>- benefits the wider health and care system;</p><p>- helps put the treatment of mental health on a par with physical health;</p><p>- will stimulate innovation and the development of new approaches to health care; or</p><p>- reduces health inequalities.</p><p> </p><p>This is in line with the agreed decision making process for new treatments in specialised services.</p><p> </p><p>During this year's decision making for potential investments in 2016/17, each of these factors were carefully considered, but did not result in any changes to the prioritisation recommendations made by CPAG.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-07-20T13:31:30.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536479/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536479/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536479/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-14","Health Services: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to NHS England's announcement of provisional investment decisions for specialised services made on 11 July 2016, whether the Clinical Priorities Advisory Group of NHS England considered any adjustments to the baseline recommendations it made on the relative prioritisation of investment in new treatments and services for 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","42841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536480","Department of Health","false","2016-07-20","<p>In the maternity pathway payment system, a multiple pregnancy would automatically lead to a higher tariff at all points of the pathway.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Improvement are currently working with the sector with a view to developing the policies to be included in the statutory consultation for the 2017/18 national tariff, including the maternity pathway system. NHS Improvement plans to publish the statutory consultation in the autumn.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-07-20T16:18:09.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536480/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536480/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-14","Multiple Births","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans NHS Improvement has to identify the cost of delivering good care in a multiple pregnancy; and whether that body intends to update the maternity tariff to reflect that cost.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Howarth","Aldershot","Sir Gerald Howarth","42826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536481","Department of Health","false","2016-07-20","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has advised that it is currently reviewing its clinical guideline on multiple pregnancy: antenatal care for twin and triplet pregnancies (CG129) to check whether an update is warranted. As part of this review, NICE will consider whether any extension of the existing scope is required. NICE expects the review decision to be published later this year.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-07-20T16:16:59.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536481/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536481/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/536481/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-14","Multiple Births","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether there are plans for NICE guidance on multiple pregnancies to be updated and extended to include provisions on the level of care to be provided during labour and birth.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Howarth","Aldershot","Sir Gerald Howarth","42827"
